23/11/2010
ZAGREB, Croatia -- Vinko Mladineo, director of the Environmental Protection and Energy Efficiency Fund, was arrested on Monday (November 22nd) as part of an investigation into the so-called Fimi Media corruption affair.
Mladineo is suspected of abuse of office and signing contracts with the Fimi Media consulting agency that helped siphon millions from state-owned companies and ministries.
(Hina, Nacional, SEEbiz, radio.net, Vecernji List - 22/11/10)
